-- AIG CEO wants firm ready for share sale ASAP
-- 
-- Thu Jan 13, 2011 7:55am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/01/13/us-aig-ceo-idUSTRE70B7SM20110113

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The chief executive officer of American International Group said in an interview that with the closing of AIG's recapitalization, the next step is a capital raise. 

 Robert Benmosche said on Wednesday he wants AIG to be ready for a share sale as soon as possible but declined to comment on a specific timing. (Reporting by  Ben Berkowitz ; Writing by  Clare Baldwin ; Editing by  Richard Chang )